window.COGNITAS_CONTENT = {"transcript":{"id":"prolanis-transcript","title":"Outpatient Prolanis Follow-up","patient":"Tn. AS","duration":"5:21","segments":[{"time":"00:00","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Selamat pagi, Pak. Silakan duduk. Kontrol Prolanis ya hari ini?","delayMs":800},{"time":"00:05","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Pagi, Dok. Iya, kontrol bulanan.","delayMs":700},{"time":"00:08","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Oke. Bapak ini sudah berapa lama kontrol di sini? DM-nya dari tahun berapa ya, saya cek dulu di sistem.","delayMs":900},{"time":"00:14","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"DM dari 2019, Dok. Hipertensi yang 2020.","delayMs":700},{"time":"00:18","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Betul, sesuai sama record. Oke. Kemarin sebulan ini ada keluhan apa, Pak? Anything bothering you?","delayMs":900},{"time":"00:25","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Anu, Dok, kadang pusing kalau bangun pagi. Sudah satu minggu ini.","delayMs":800},{"time":"00:31","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Pusingnya seperti apa? Berputar gitu — vertigo — atau cuma rasa goyang aja?","delayMs":800},{"time":"00:37","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Goyang aja, Dok. Bangun dari tempat tidur kadang, atau dari duduk lama. Gak sampai jatuh sih.","delayMs":800},{"time":"00:44","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Hmm, oke.","delayMs":600},{"time":"00:45","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Ada keluhan lain? Dada berdebar, sesak, nyeri dada?","delayMs":700},{"time":"00:49","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Tidak ada, Dok.","delayMs":500},{"time":"00:51","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Mual? Muntah? Telinga berdenging?","delayMs":600},{"time":"00:54","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Tidak.","delayMs":500},{"time":"00:55","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"BAK gimana — masih sering banget kayak dulu? Polidipsi-polyuria-nya?","delayMs":800},{"time":"01:00","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Sudah jauh berkurang, Dok. Sejak rutin minum obat itu.","delayMs":700},{"time":"01:05","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Obatnya rutin ya, Pak? Tidak ada yang skip? Compliance-nya bagus?","delayMs":800},{"time":"01:10","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Rutin, Dok. Hampir tidak pernah lupa.","delayMs":600},{"time":"01:13","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Mantap. Diet bagaimana?","delayMs":600},{"time":"01:16","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Diet, Dok... masih kadang-kadang nasi putihnya banyak. Kalau ada acara keluarga gitu suka jebol.","delayMs":900},{"time":"01:23","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Jebol. Olahraga?","delayMs":600},{"time":"01:26","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Jalan kaki tiga kali seminggu, 30 menit kira-kira.","delayMs":700},{"time":"01:32","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Bagus, sudah memenuhi target Prolanis. Targetnya 150 menit per minggu. Oke. Sekarang saya periksa dulu ya. Suster, tolong tensi-nya dulu.","delayMs":1000},{"time":"01:43","speaker":"SUSTER","text":"Baik, Dok. Pak, lengan kanan ya, tarik napas santai aja.","delayMs":700},{"time":"01:48","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Sambil itu, Pak, berat badan tadi ditimbang di depan?","delayMs":700},{"time":"01:52","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"78 kilo, Dok.","delayMs":500},{"time":"01:54","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"78 kilo. Tinggi 168 ya, bapak? BMI-nya... 27.6. Masih overweight. Target turun 5 kilo dulu lah ya.","delayMs":1000},{"time":"02:03","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Susah, Dok.","delayMs":500},{"time":"02:05","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Saya tahu. Tapi every kilo turun, HbA1c bisa turun setengah persen kira-kira. Worth it. Sus, TD-nya berapa?","delayMs":900},{"time":"02:15","speaker":"SUSTER","text":"148/92, Dok. Heart rate 84.","delayMs":700},{"time":"02:18","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"148/92. Hmm, naik dari bulan lalu yang 138/88. Oke. Sekarang fisik dulu ya. Buka kancing atas, Pak. Tarik napas dalam. Bagus. Sekali lagi. Batuk. Cor S1 S2 reguler, no murmur. Pulmo vesikuler, ronchi negatif. Perut dulu — tekan di sini sakit gak?","delayMs":1200},{"time":"02:42","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Gak, Dok.","delayMs":500},{"time":"02:43","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Sini? Bagus, gak ada masalah. Hepar lien tidak teraba. Kaki, monofilamen test ya — tutup mata, kasih tahu kalau terasa.","delayMs":900},{"time":"02:52","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Terasa. Terasa. Terasa.","delayMs":600},{"time":"02:55","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Semua titik bagus. Tidak ada diabetic neuropathy yet. Akral hangat, denyut dorsalis pedis bagus, no ulkus. Bagus.","delayMs":900},{"time":"03:05","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Sekarang lab-nya kita lihat. Bulan ini... GDP 142, GD2PP 198. Hmm. HbA1c 7.4. Target kita di bawah 7. Naik dari bulan lalu yang 7.1.","delayMs":1100},{"time":"03:21","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Naik, Dok?","delayMs":500},{"time":"03:23","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Naik sedikit. Mungkin karena nasi putih jebol-nya ya. LDL 132, masih agak tinggi. Kreatinin 1.0, eGFR 78 — ginjal masih baik. Tapi urin ada protein, satu plus. Microalbuminuria.","delayMs":1200},{"time":"03:40","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Ini early sign DKD — diabetic kidney disease. Belum confirmed, kita perlu UACR — urine albumin-creatinine ratio — untuk konfirmasi. Bulan depan saya cek lagi.","delayMs":1000},{"time":"03:50","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Iya, Dok.","delayMs":500},{"time":"03:52","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Oke. Plan-nya begini, Pak. Obat-obatannya saya lanjut dulu — tetap sama. Metformin 500 mg TID, sesudah makan. Glimepiride 2 mg OD AM, sebelum makan. Amlodipine 5 mg pagi. Captopril 25 mg BID, sebelum makan. Simvastatin 20 mg malam. Sama Aspirin 80 mg pagi.","delayMs":1300},{"time":"04:18","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Tetap sama semua, Dok?","delayMs":500},{"time":"04:20","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Tetap. Tapi kalau TD masih tinggi terus bulan depan, kita pertimbangkan ganti Captopril ke Lisinopril yang sekali sehari aja, biar lebih convenient. Kita lihat dulu.","delayMs":1000},{"time":"04:32","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Oke.","delayMs":500},{"time":"04:33","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Edukasi ya: bangun dari tempat tidur perlahan-lahan, hitung 30 detik sebelum berdiri, biar pusingnya hilang. Itu kemungkinan orthostatic hypotension karena obat anti-hipertensinya kuat. Minum cukup, 1.5 L/hari, jangan dehidrasi. Diet tetap DM 1700 kalori, perbanyak sayur dan protein lean.","delayMs":1200},{"time":"04:55","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Tekanan darah tolong dicatat di rumah, pagi dan sore, selama satu minggu, bawa ke kontrol berikutnya. Ada tensimeter di rumah?","delayMs":900},{"time":"05:01","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Ada, anak saya beliin.","delayMs":500},{"time":"05:03","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Bagus. Kontrol Prolanis bulan depan ya, Pak. Sebelum kontrol, cek lagi: HbA1c, profil lipid, dan tambah UACR — itu yang microalbumin-nya. Ada pertanyaan?","delayMs":1000},{"time":"05:14","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Tidak, Dok. Cukup jelas.","delayMs":500},{"time":"05:16","speaker":"DOKTER","text":"Oke. Resep saya tulis sekarang. Hati-hati di jalan ya, Pak. Sampai bulan depan.","delayMs":800},{"time":"05:21","speaker":"PASIEN","text":"Terima kasih, Dok.","delayMs":600}]},"soap":{"id":"prolanis-soap","title":"Outpatient Note — Prolanis Follow-up","patient":{"name":"Tn. AS","mrn":"RM-2026-0034812","age":58,"sex":"Male","facility":"Klinik Platinum Alfa (FKTP)","visitDate":"10 June 2026","visitType":"Outpatient — Prolanis Monthly Control"},"soapDelayMs":3000,"sections":[{"key":"S","title":"SUBJECTIVE","delayMs":0,"blocks":[{"label":"Chief complaint","text":"Pusing saat bangun pagi/dari duduk, 1 minggu","delayMs":400},{"label":"HPI","text":"Vertigo-like dizziness on position change. No palpitation, dyspnea, chest pain, nausea, tinnitus, or pre-syncope. Polydipsia-polyuria improved since on OAD.","delayMs":600},{"label":"Compliance","text":"Good — almost no missed doses (self-reported)","delayMs":400},{"label":"Diet","text":"Partially adherent; episodic excess white rice at family events","delayMs":400},{"label":"Exercise","text":"Walking 3×/week × 30 min ≈ 90 min/wk (Prolanis target 150 min not yet met)","delayMs":500}]},{"key":"O","title":"OBJECTIVE","delayMs":800,"blocks":[{"label":"BP","text":"148/92 mmHg (↑ from 138/88 last month)","delayMs":400},{"label":"HR","text":"84/min, regular","delayMs":300},{"label":"Weight / Height / BMI","text":"78 kg / 168 cm / BMI 27.6 (overweight)","delayMs":400},{"label":"Cardiovascular","text":"S1 S2 regular, no murmur","delayMs":300},{"label":"Pulmonary","text":"Vesicular breath sounds, ronchi (−/−)","delayMs":300},{"label":"Abdomen","text":"Soft, non-tender, liver/spleen not palpable","delayMs":300},{"label":"Diabetic foot exam","text":"10g monofilament intact (no neuropathy); warm extremities, dorsalis pedis pulse intact, no ulcer","delayMs":500},{"label":"Labs (today)","text":"GDP 142 mg/dL | GD2PP 198 mg/dL | HbA1c 7.4% (↑ from 7.1%) | LDL 132 mg/dL | Creatinine 1.0 mg/dL | eGFR 78 mL/min/1.73m² | Urinalysis: Protein +1 (microalbuminuria, UACR pending)","delayMs":700}]},{"key":"A","title":"ASSESSMENT","delayMs":600,"blocks":[{"label":"1","text":"T2DM, uncontrolled (HbA1c rising) — ICD-10: E11.9","delayMs":400},{"label":"2","text":"Hypertension grade 1, uncontrolled — ICD-10: I10","delayMs":400},{"label":"3","text":"Mixed dyslipidemia — ICD-10: E78.2","delayMs":300},{"label":"4","text":"Overweight — ICD-10: E66.3","delayMs":300},{"label":"5","text":"Suspected early diabetic nephropathy (microalbuminuria, eGFR preserved) — ICD-10: E11.21 (candidate, pending UACR)","delayMs":500},{"label":"6","text":"Probable orthostatic hypotension (dizziness on standing, on multi-antihypertensive regimen) — ICD-10: I95.1","delayMs":500}]},{"key":"P","title":"PLAN","delayMs":600,"blocks":[{"label":"Pharmacology (continue)","text":"Metformin 500 mg PO TID after meals | Glimepiride 2 mg PO OD AM before meal | Amlodipine 5 mg PO OD AM | Captopril 25 mg PO BID before meals | Simvastatin 20 mg PO OD PM | Aspirin 80 mg PO OD","delayMs":600},{"label":"Conditional change","text":"Captopril 25 mg BID → Lisinopril 10 mg OD if BP remains uncontrolled next visit","delayMs":400},{"label":"Non-pharmacological","text":"Slow rise from supine/seated (count 30s) | Fluid intake 1.5 L/day | DM diet 1700 kcal/day, increase vegetables and lean protein | Home BP monitoring AM + PM × 1 week","delayMs":500},{"label":"Follow-up","text":"Next visit: 1 month (Prolanis) | Repeat: HbA1c, lipid panel, UACR | Patient brings home BP log and medication log","delayMs":500}]}]},"prolanisCoding":{"id":"prolanis-coding","recordId":"prolanis-note","title":"Prolanis Note","subtitle":"T2DM + Hypertension — Outpatient Consultation","patient":{"name":"Tn. AS","mrn":"RM-2026-0034812","age":58,"sex":"Male","bpjs":"Active, Class 2"},"physicianDiagnoses":[{"rank":1,"text":"Diabetes Mellitus type 2, uncontrolled","icd10":null},{"rank":2,"text":"Hypertension grade 1, uncontrolled","icd10":null},{"rank":3,"text":"Mixed dyslipidemia","icd10":null},{"rank":4,"text":"Overweight","icd10":null}],"aiDiagnoses":[{"rank":1,"type":"primary","text":"Type 2 diabetes mellitus without complications","icd10":"E11.9","evidence":"HbA1c 7.4% (target <7.0), GDP 142 mg/dL, GD2PP 198 mg/dL — uncontrolled glycaemia documented in today's labs and assessment."},{"rank":2,"type":"secondary","text":"Essential (primary) hypertension","icd10":"I10","evidence":"BP 148/92 mmHg, elevated from 138/88 last month; on Amlodipine + Captopril; addressed in today's plan."},{"rank":3,"type":"secondary","text":"Mixed hyperlipidaemia","icd10":"E78.2","evidence":"LDL 132 mg/dL on lipid profile; Simvastatin 20 mg continued in prescription."},{"rank":4,"type":"secondary","text":"Overweight","icd10":"E66.3","evidence":"BMI 27.6 (78 kg / 168 cm); weight management discussed in plan."},{"rank":5,"type":"candidate","text":"Type 2 DM with diabetic nephropathy","icd10":"E11.21","evidence":"Urinalysis protein +1 (microalbuminuria). UACR not yet quantified — upgrade to E11.21 if UACR ≥30 mg/g confirmed at next visit. Would shift INA-CBG grouping.","flag":"Candidate upgrade — pending UACR confirmation"}],"procedures":[],"claimType":"Prolanis FKTP capitation (non-claimable per-visit)","inaCbgNote":"Primary E11.9 selected because DKD not yet confirmed (dipstick only, no UACR)."},"tbCoding":{"id":"tb-discharge-coding","recordId":"tb-discharge","title":"TB Discharge Summary","subtitle":"Pulmonary TB — Inpatient Discharge","patient":{"name":"Tn. BP","mrn":"RM-2026-0012847","age":52,"sex":"Male","bpjs":"Active, Class 2"},"physicianDiagnoses":[{"rank":1,"text":"TB Paru Kasus Baru, BTA (+/+/+), klinis sedang","icd10":null},{"rank":2,"text":"Diabetes Mellitus type 2, newly diagnosed","icd10":null},{"rank":3,"text":"Mild normocytic normochromic anaemia","icd10":null}],"aiDiagnoses":[{"rank":1,"type":"primary","text":"Tuberculosis of lung, confirmed by sputum microscopy","icd10":"A15.0","evidence":"BTA sputum SPS +++/+++/++; GeneXpert MTB detected, Rifampicin sensitive; chest X-ray infiltrate patchy right upper lobe with fibrocavitation."},{"rank":2,"type":"secondary","text":"Type 2 diabetes mellitus without complications","icd10":"E11.9","evidence":"GDP 168 mg/dL, HbA1c 8.2% on admission labs; Metformin 500 mg initiated during stay."},{"rank":3,"type":"secondary","text":"Anaemia, unspecified","icd10":"D64.9","evidence":"Hb 10.2 g/dL on admission; Sulfas Ferrosus 300 mg prescribed at discharge."}],"procedures":[{"text":"Sputum BTA examination, 3 specimens","icd9":"87.42","evidence":"BTA sputum SPS performed ×3 during diagnostic workup (Section V, discharge summary)."},{"text":"Chest X-ray PA","icd9":"87.44","evidence":"Foto thorax PA: infiltrate patchy right upper lobe, fibrocavitation (+)."},{"text":"TB-DOTS education and PMO counselling","icd9":"89.07","evidence":"Edukasi TB-DOTS and PMO assignment to spouse documented in discharge plan (Section X)."}],"claimType":"INA-CBGs Group A-4-12-II (Moderate TB infection)","inaCbgNote":"A15.0 selected (sputum-confirmed) vs A15.1 (culture-confirmed) vs A15.2 (histologically-confirmed)."},"geriatricCdss":{"id":"geriatric-cdss","recordId":"geriatric-polypharmacy","title":"Geriatric Polypharmacy Case","patient":{"name":"Ny. KW","age":72,"sex":"Female","weight":"62 kg","bmi":25.5,"egfr":48,"comorbidities":"HT, T2DM, CKD stage 3a, right knee OA, BPH-like LUTS"},"medications":[{"name":"Amlodipine 10 mg","dose":"1× daily AM","indication":"Hypertension"},{"name":"Captopril 25 mg","dose":"3× daily (a.c.)","indication":"Hypertension + CKD"},{"name":"Furosemide 40 mg","dose":"1× daily AM","indication":"Edema (historical)"},{"name":"Metformin 500 mg","dose":"2× daily","indication":"T2DM"},{"name":"Glibenclamide 5 mg","dose":"1× daily AM (a.c.)","indication":"T2DM"},{"name":"Meloxicam 7.5 mg","dose":"PRN","indication":"Knee OA"},{"name":"Tamsulosin 0.4 mg","dose":"1× nightly","indication":"LUTS (off-label, female)"},{"name":"Aspirin 80 mg","dose":"1× daily (OTC)","indication":"Self-initiated"},{"name":"Glucosamine + chondroitin","dose":"1× daily (OTC)","indication":"Joint health"}],"searchDatabases":["PubMed","Lexicomp","Micromedex","Beers Criteria 2023","Fornas DDI Reference"],"severitySummary":"SEVERE — 3 hard alerts, 2 high alerts requiring immediate deprescribing review","streamBlocks":[{"type":"heading","text":"Clinical Decision Support — Drug Interaction & Deprescribing Analysis","delayMs":500},{"type":"summary","text":"72-year-old female with CKD stage 3a (eGFR 48), orthostatic hypotension (systolic drop 26 mmHg on standing), and 9 concurrent medications from 3 prescribers. Primary concern today: orthostatic dizziness × 2 weeks.","delayMs":800},{"type":"alert","severity":"severe","title":"DRP-1: Glibenclamide + eGFR 48 + age 72","text":"Long-acting sulfonylurea in elderly with reduced renal function — high risk of severe, prolonged hypoglycaemia.","mechanism":"Glibenclamide has active metabolites renally excreted; impaired clearance at eGFR <60 prolongs hypoglycaemic effect.","recommendation":"STOP Glibenclamide. Replace with Linagliptin 5 mg OD (no renal dose adjustment required).","reference":"Beers Criteria 2023 — avoid long-acting sulfonylureas in adults ≥65.","delayMs":1000},{"type":"alert","severity":"severe","title":"DRP-4: Triple Whammy — NSAID + ACE-I + Diuretic on CKD","text":"Meloxicam (NSAID) + Captopril (ACE-I) + Furosemide on eGFR 48 — severe AKI risk.","mechanism":"ACE-I reduces efferent arteriolar tone; diuretic causes volume depletion; NSAID blocks prostaglandin-mediated afferent vasodilation — combined effect sharply reduces GFR.","recommendation":"STOP Meloxicam. Replace with Paracetamol 500 mg PRN (max 3 g/day) + topical Diclofenac gel for knee.","reference":"Triple whammy AKI — well-documented in CKD populations (eGFR <60).","delayMs":1000},{"type":"alert","severity":"high","title":"DRP-5: Tamsulosin in female patient — off-label","text":"α1-blocker prescribed for LUTS in female — likely mis-prescribed; major contributor to orthostatic hypotension.","mechanism":"α1-adrenergic blockade causes vasodilation and postural BP drop, compounded by antihypertensives and diuretic.","recommendation":"STOP Tamsulosin pending urology verification. Observe orthostatic symptoms for 1 week.","reference":"Tamsulosin is indicated for BPH in males; off-label use in females requires specialist confirmation.","delayMs":900},{"type":"alert","severity":"high","title":"DRP-2: Furosemide without active indication","text":"Routine loop diuretic without current edema — contributes to volume depletion and orthostatic hypotension.","mechanism":"Volume depletion reduces preload; combined with antihypertensives and α-blocker worsens postural BP drop.","recommendation":"STOP or reduce to PRN only if edema recurs.","reference":"Orthostatic hypotension polypharmacy: ≥2 antihypertensives + α1-blocker + diuretic.","delayMs":800},{"type":"alert","severity":"moderate","title":"DRP-6: Aspirin without primary prevention indication","text":"Self-purchased aspirin in 72-year-old with no CV event history — bleeding risk outweighs benefit.","mechanism":"Primary prevention aspirin in elderly increases GI bleeding risk without proven CV benefit in this profile.","recommendation":"STOP aspirin. Educate patient on lack of indication.","reference":"ASPREE trial and current guidelines — avoid primary prevention aspirin in adults >70 without high CV risk.","delayMs":700},{"type":"alert","severity":"advisory","title":"DRP-3: Captopril TID dosing in elderly","text":"Short-acting ACE-I with suboptimal adherence in elderly — consider once-daily alternative.","mechanism":"TID dosing reduces compliance; trough BP control may be inadequate.","recommendation":"Switch Captopril 25 mg TID → Lisinopril 10 mg OD.","reference":"Fornas preference for once-daily antihypertensives in chronic disease management.","delayMs":600},{"type":"heading","text":"Recommended Regimen After Deprescribing (9 → 4 core drugs)","delayMs":500},{"type":"list","items":["Amlodipine 5 mg — 1× daily AM (reduced from 10 mg)","Lisinopril 10 mg — 1× daily AM (replaces Captopril)","Metformin 500 mg — 2× daily (continue)","Linagliptin 5 mg — 1× daily (replaces Glibenclamide)","Paracetamol 500 mg PRN — max 3 g/day (replaces Meloxicam)","Topical Diclofenac gel — PRN for knee"],"delayMs":800}],"references":[{"title":"Beers Criteria 2023 — American Geriatrics Society","detail":"Avoid long-acting sulfonylureas (Glibenclamide) in adults ≥65 with CKD."},{"title":"Triple Whammy AKI — Nephrology literature review","detail":"ACE-I/ARB + diuretic + NSAID combination in CKD stage 3+ — incidence and prevention."},{"title":"Fornas 2024 — Formularium Nasional","detail":"Linagliptin, Lisinopril dosing guidance for Indonesian BPJS facilities."}]},"prolanisCdss":{"id":"prolanis-cdss","recordId":"prolanis-note","title":"Prolanis Follow-up — Medication Review","patient":{"name":"Tn. AS","age":58,"sex":"Male","egfr":78,"comorbidities":"T2DM, Hypertension, Dyslipidemia"},"medications":[{"name":"Metformin 500 mg","dose":"TID after meals","indication":"T2DM"},{"name":"Glimepiride 2 mg","dose":"1× daily AM","indication":"T2DM"},{"name":"Amlodipine 5 mg","dose":"1× daily AM","indication":"Hypertension"},{"name":"Captopril 25 mg","dose":"BID before meals","indication":"Hypertension"},{"name":"Simvastatin 20 mg","dose":"1× nightly","indication":"Dyslipidemia"},{"name":"Aspirin 80 mg","dose":"1× daily","indication":"Cardioprotection"}],"searchDatabases":["PubMed","Lexicomp","Micromedex","FDA Drug Safety","Fornas DDI Reference"],"severitySummary":"ADVISORY — 2 monitored interactions, no blocking alerts","streamBlocks":[{"type":"heading","text":"Clinical Decision Support — Medication Interaction Analysis","delayMs":500},{"type":"summary","text":"58-year-old male on 6 medications for Prolanis (T2DM + HTN). eGFR 78 mL/min — renal function adequate. New complaint: orthostatic dizziness × 1 week.","delayMs":700},{"type":"alert","severity":"advisory","title":"Captopril + Aspirin","text":"Theoretical reduced ACE-I efficacy; renal vasoconstriction risk in dehydration.","mechanism":"Aspirin may attenuate ACE-I mediated prostaglandin synthesis; clinically modest at low-dose aspirin.","recommendation":"Monitor BP and renal function. Ensure adequate hydration (1.5 L/day as advised). No change required today.","reference":"Advisory level — not blocking. Common co-prescription in cardiovascular risk patients.","delayMs":800},{"type":"alert","severity":"monitored","title":"Simvastatin 20 mg + Amlodipine 5 mg","text":"Current Simvastatin dose at FDA advisory ceiling when combined with Amlodipine.","mechanism":"Amlodipine inhibits CYP3A4, increasing Simvastatin exposure and myopathy risk at doses >20 mg.","recommendation":"Maintain Simvastatin at ≤20 mg (current dose acceptable). Monitor for myalgia. Do not increase Simvastatin dose.","reference":"FDA 2011 Drug Safety Communication — Simvastatin dose limit with Amlodipine.","delayMs":800},{"type":"alert","severity":"advisory","title":"Glimepiride in 58 y/o — monitor if eGFR declines","text":"Sulfonylurea acceptable at current eGFR 78; re-evaluate if eGFR falls below 60.","mechanism":"Reduced renal clearance of active metabolites increases hypoglycaemia risk as eGFR declines.","recommendation":"Continue current dose. Recheck eGFR at next Prolanis visit. Consider DPP-4 inhibitor if eGFR <60.","reference":"Beers Criteria — caution with sulfonylureas when eGFR <60 or age >65.","delayMs":700},{"type":"alert","severity":"advisory","title":"Polypharmacy contribution to orthostatic symptoms","text":"5 drugs affecting BP/glycaemia — likely contributor to reported morning dizziness.","mechanism":"Combined antihypertensive effect (Amlodipine + Captopril) with orthostatic challenge.","recommendation":"Non-pharmacological measures advised (slow rise, 30s count). Planned Captopril → Lisinopril switch if BP uncontrolled next visit.","reference":"Doctor stated conditional switch to Lisinopril 10 mg OD for adherence if BP remains elevated.","delayMs":700}],"references":[{"title":"FDA Drug Safety Communication (2011)","detail":"Simvastatin 80 mg contraindicated with Amlodipine; limit to 20 mg."},{"title":"ACE-I + Antiplatelet Interaction Review","detail":"Low-dose aspirin co-prescription with ACE-I — clinical significance and monitoring."}]},"chatPresets":{"analysisDelayMs":2200,"streamCharDelayMs":16,"presets":[{"id":"greeting","match":["hello","hi","hey","halo","good morning","good afternoon"],"matchType":"includes","reply":"Hello! I'm your clinical AI assistant, focused on medical record documentation, clinical Q&A, and literature search. How can I help with your medical questions today?"},{"id":"prolanis","match":["prolanis","diabetes","hba1c","t2dm","blood pressure","hypertension"],"matchType":"includes","reply":"For the Prolanis follow-up case (Tn. AS, 58 y/o): today's labs show HbA1c 7.4% (rising from 7.1%), BP 148/92 mmHg, and urinalysis protein +1 suggesting early DKD. Primary coding: E11.9 with candidate upgrade to E11.21 pending UACR. Would you like to open Ambient AI for live note capture, or run Insurance Coding?"},{"id":"insurance","match":["insurance","coding","icd","icd-10","bpjs","ina-cbg","claim"],"matchType":"includes","reply":"I can generate an INA-CBG / BPJS coding report from a clinical record. Available presets: Prolanis Note (E11.9 + I10 + E78.2 + E66.3) and TB Discharge (A15.0 + E11.9 + D64.9 with ICD-9-CM procedures). Click Insurance Assistant below or type \"run insurance coding\" to start."},{"id":"drug","match":["drug","medication","interaction","prescription","polypharmacy","cdss","ddi"],"matchType":"includes","reply":"I can run a Clinical Decision Support review for drug interactions. The geriatric case (Ny. KW, 72 y/o, 9 medications) flags severe alerts: Glibenclamide + eGFR 48 (Beers Criteria), triple whammy NSAID+ACE-I+diuretic, and off-label Tamsulosin. Click Clinical Assistant to run the full analysis."},{"id":"ambient","match":["ambient","transcription","soap","outpatient record","write record","ai writing"],"matchType":"includes","reply":"Ambient AI can capture the Prolanis consultation live — mixed Bahasa/English transcription streams on the left while a structured SOAP note generates on the right. Click AI Writing to launch the outpatient record demo."},{"id":"tb","match":["tuberculosis","tb","discharge","bta","oat"],"matchType":"includes","reply":"The TB discharge summary case includes primary diagnosis A15.0 (sputum-confirmed pulmonary TB), secondary E11.9 and D64.9, plus procedures 87.42, 87.44, and 89.07 for INA-CBGs Group A-4-12-II. Select TB Discharge in Insurance Coding to view the full report."}],"defaultReply":"I'm your Cognitas clinical AI assistant. I can help with ambient documentation (AI Writing), insurance coding (ICD-10 / ICD-9-CM), and clinical decision support for drug interactions. Try asking about Prolanis, insurance coding, or medication review — or use the quick-action tags below."}};
